summary:
(FM-84)  

Standing on a skyline Watching all the cars go Sleeping in the daylight You're losing all control I can't stand to...
track_name: 07 - Wild Ones (feat. Ollie Wride) **Album OUT NOW**
caption:
(FM-84)

Standing on a skyline
Watching all the cars go
Sleeping in the daylight
You’re losing all control
I can’t stand to see it
Watching you fall apart
I never wanted to be
Anything you are

I bet you think you’re pretty dangerous
Burning down the walls
Breaking all the laws, yeah?
Has there ever been a time for us?
I guess that I’ll never tell

Wild ones, we’re wild ones
Oh oh we don’t care what you think of us now
Wild ones, we’re wild ones
Oh Oh, we don’t keep ourselves to the ground

Running through the back streets
Like the videos on TV
It was just another blowout
That we forgot to leave

I bet you think you’re pretty dangerous
Burning down the walls
Breaking all the laws, yeah?
Has there ever been a time for us?
I guess that I’ll never tell

Wild ones, we’re wild ones
Oh oh we don’t care what you think of us now
Wild ones, we’re wild ones
Oh Oh, we don’t keep ourselves to the ground

I hear your heart tremble like a storm
In the cold of night
You must be keeping something from the world
See, I’m holding to the edges of the light you leave behind
I love that you’re a wild one
Show me you’re a wild one, tonight

https://beardoftormund.tumblr.com/post/185185060113/ahem
But leading up to Jon and...
body:
A follow up on free folk dances…

Inspired by this genius from @beardoftormund

https://beardoftormund.tumblr.com/post/185185060113/ahem

But leading up to Jon and Tormund’s wedding, Jon wants to get better at the folk dances and learn the specific wedding dance, etc…

So who better to enlist to teach him than Tormund’s daughters???? And it’s just like that one scene in footloose with the little girls teaching the guy to dance

Then after their wedding and the dance Tormund’s shocked by how well Jon knew all the different dances, and he’s about to ask him where he learnt them when the girls come running at Jon giggling and shouting how proud they are of him.

The four of them spend the rest of the night dancing together until the girls are asleep on their feet and are taken off to bed, leaving the newlyweds to dance alone ;)

AHEM

summary:
Sansa stans: Don't blame S8 for Kit's breakdown.
Kit: Says season finale is disappointing. Cries when he reads the scripts....
body:
Sansa stans: Don’t blame S8 for Kit’s breakdown.

Kit: Says season finale is disappointing. Cries when he reads the scripts. Tells interviews the season was meant to break the actors. Couldn’t even make it to the airing of the finale before checking into rehab. Yada yada yada yada. And let’s not forget how even Emilia cried and called her parents.

So hell yes, I am going to blame D&D and their shit ending for contributing heavily to his breakdown. He - and Emilia - deserved better.

I don’t think it’s a joke in the slightest.
